  "id": "multiply",
  "title": "multiply",
  "lastModified": "2026-02-11T11:34:29.081876-05:00",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "TEXT",
      "value": "<p>Computes the product of all inputs. You can pass any number of scalars or series: multiply(a, b, c) = a × b × c. When filter=true, NaNs are replaced with 1 before the product; when false, any NaN propagates to the result.</p><p>Example calculations:</p><ul><li>multiply(2, 3) = 6</li><li>multiply(2, 3, 4) = 24</li><li>multiply(5, NaN, filter=false) = NaN</li></ul><p>multiply(5, NaN, filter=true) = 5 × 1 = 5</p>",
      "id": "7d416569-256a-4490-9fd1-007e1168cfa5"
    },
